<TD WIDTH="510"><center><a href="merger.htm"><img src="/graphics/twosigns.gif" width="432" height="324" border="0" alt="Ultramar Diamond Shamrock Corp."></a></center>
<center><h1>Diamond Shamrock<br> and Ultramar Merge</h1></center><p>
<Table border="0"  width="504">
 <tr>

<td>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

The <a href="merger.htm">merger</a> of Diamond Shamrock, Inc. and Ultramar Corporation on December 3, 1996,  created one of the largest independent petroleum and marketing companies in North America.  With four refineries, a network of approximately 4,400 outlets in 10 Southwestern states and eastern Canada, and a mix of related businesses, Ultramar Diamond Shamrock Corporation is postured for growth.<p>
<p><hr><p><h1 align="center">
ULTRAMAR DIAMOND SHAMROCK COMPLETES
ACQUISITION OF TOTAL PETROLEUM
</h1><p>

San Antonio, Texas -- Sept. 25, 1997--Ultramar Diamond Shamrock (NYSE: UDS) today completed its <a href="p092597.htm">acquisition of Total</a> Petroleum (North America) Ltd. (AMEX:TPN). 
In connection with the acquisition, UDS has issued .322 shares of its common stock for each of Total Petroleum’s 39 million outstanding shares and assumed approximately $435 million of Total Petroleum debt.

